Tool                     Purpose
curl               Transfer data to/from servers
nc (netcat)         Raw TCP/UDP connections
openssl s_client    Test SSL/TLS encrypted connections
nmap                Scan networks and ports
telnet              Connect to remote hosts (unencrypted)
ports               Doors that services listen on 

###PORTS
Well Known Ports:
Port      Service          Protocol  
21         FTP          File transfer
22         SSH          Secure remote login
23        Telnet        Unsecure remote login
25         SMTP          Sending email
53         DNS           Domain name lookup
80        HTTP           Web traffic
443       HTTPS         Secure web traffic
3306      MySQL          Database
8080      HTTP         altDev web servers

PORT RANGES
0    - 1023   → System/well-known ports (need root)
1024 - 49151  → Registered ports (applications)
49152 - 65535 → Dynamic/private ports (temporary)

###Curl 
Transfer Data From Servers -it fetches web content from the terminal.
curl [flags] [URL]
Common flags:
Flag      Meaning                                  Example
-v       verbose, show full connection details   curl -v google.com
-I       fetch headers only                       curl -I google.com
-L        follow redirects                        curl -L google.com #usually used when url has been changed and redirects, instead of break, it goes. 
-o      save output to file                       curl -o page.html google.com
-O      save with original filename               curl -O example.com/file.zip
-u      username:password auth                    curl -u user:pass example.com
-X      specify HTTP method                       curl -X POST example.com
-d      send data (POST body)                     curl -d "name=John" example.com
-H      add custom header                         curl -H "Authorization: Bearer token"
-k      ignore SSL certificate errors             curl -k https://example.com
-s      silent mode, no progress bar              curl -s example.com
